

                Shopping Guide            
By                     
                                    TIM McKEOUGH
                            
                APRIL 9, 2018
    
Slipper chairs come in many variations, but they all share a defining characteristic.
“It’s an armless lounge chair,” said Damon Liss, an interior designer in New York.
Still, a slipper chair isn’t merely an exercise in subtraction. By forgoing armrests, it adds something crucial to a room: a relaxed sense of style.
“There are a lot of places, especially in apartments, where you want something that is visually lighter” than an armchair, said Mr. Liss, who frequently uses slipper chairs in living rooms and bedrooms. “It’s the concept of balance: If you have lots of pieces with lots of arms everywhere, it can get too busy.”
From a functional standpoint, a slipper chair is “easy to flop into” from almost any direction, he said, because there are no arms to hurdle.
Advertisement
And it also provides an excuse to cozy up to a loved one, he pointed out: “Two people can easily sit on one.”
