• What should you look for when you’re choosing a slipper chair? “Because there are no arms, you need to have interest from something else — maybe it’s a beautiful fabric,” Mr. Liss said, but it could also be an interesting wooden frame.
Advertisement
• How laid-back should it be? “You see them upright and more lounge-y,” Mr. Liss said, but he usually prefers the latter, with a more reclined back.
• What is the ideal seat height? “About 15 or 16 inches high,” he said.
